#!/usr/bin/env -S uv run --script
# /// script
# requires-python = ">=3.11"
# dependencies = [
#     "telethon>=1.36",
# ]
# ///
"""
telegram — agent-first CLI for a personal Telegram account (MTProto, full account).

This tool is designed to be invoked by agents. Run `telegram help` to load the full
usage contract on demand — do not rely on memorised knowledge of its surface.

Agent startup protocol (this is a STATEFUL CLI — it holds a login session):
  1. Run `telegram doctor` first. It proves the chain: credentials resolve, Telegram
     is reachable, and the session is authorized.
  2. Exit 2 from doctor means the session is missing or expired — run
     `telegram login` (interactive: prompts for phone, the code Telegram sends, and a
     2FA password if set). Login persists the session file; later commands reuse
     it with no prompt.
  3. A healthy `telegram doctor` (exit 0) means ready to work.

Configuration resolves as connections — named, complete resolutions of the app
credentials and the session. With no registry there is one implicit connection,
`default`, resolved by the cascade (first non-empty wins): the `--session` flag
(session path only) > a project .env(.local) > ~/.config/telegram/credentials.env
> the process environment. Secrets (TELEGRAM_API_HASH, DEEPGRAM_API_KEY) have no
flag — only their env-var NAME resolves them, never the command line.

More than one account is declared in a connections registry — project
.capabilities/telegram/connections.json, else the machine-level
~/.config/telegram/connections.json (the natural home for a personal account),
first found wins. Each entry names its app id literally and its app hash by
env-key indirection, and owns a per-connection session:

  {
    "default": "main",
    "connections": {
      "main": { "api_id": 1234567, "secret_env": "TELEGRAM_API_HASH" },
      "work": { "api_id": 7654321, "secret_env": "TELEGRAM_WORK_HASH",
                "allow_write": true }
    }
  }

The write gate: a `send` leaves the system (a message to a person), so it is off
unless a connection grants it. The implicit default cannot send; grant it with
`"allow_write": true` on a connection in connections.json. A refused write exits
4 — ask the user, never lift the gate yourself.

  --connection <id>        Select a connection; accepted by every verb. Optional
                           with a default pointer or a sole connection.
  TELEGRAM_API_ID          Numeric app id from my.telegram.org/apps (implicit
                           default; a registry entry names `api_id` instead).
  TELEGRAM_API_HASH        App hash paired with the id (secret).
  TELEGRAM_SESSION         Session path, no extension — Telethon writes
                           <path>.session on disk. Optional one-shot override; the
                           default connection's session defaults to
                           $XDG_STATE_HOME/telegram/session, a named connection's
                           to <state-dir>/<id>/session.
  DEEPGRAM_API_KEY         Required only by `transcribe` (secret).

  --session <PATH>         One-shot override of the session-file path, accepted
                           anywhere on the line. Names a path, not a secret.

Commands:
  telegram help                                Print this document.
  telegram doctor                              Health check: creds + reachability + session.
  telegram login                               Interactive first-time auth (phone + code).
  telegram whoami                              Identity of the signed-in account.
  telegram chats [--limit N]                   List recent dialogs.
  telegram read <chat> [--limit N] [--since ISO] [--json]
                                               Read messages from a chat.
  telegram search <chat> <query> [--limit N] [--json]
                                               Search messages inside a chat.
  telegram send <chat> <text>                  Send a message.
  telegram export <chat> --out PATH [--media-dir PATH] [--limit N] [--since ISO]
            [--no-photos] [--no-stickers] [--videos] [--documents]
                                               Dump full history to JSON; download
                                               voice/audio (+photos/stickers by
                                               default) to media-dir; leave
                                               transcription placeholders.
  telegram transcribe <json_path> [--force] [--model nova-3]
                                               Fill transcription placeholders in an
                                               exported JSON via Deepgram (audio
                                               referenced by media.file_path).

Chat references:
  <chat> can be @username, a phone (+1555…), a numeric id, or a chat title
  (case-insensitive substring matched against your dialog list).

I/O contract:
  - Success: JSON on stdout, exit 0. (`read`/`search` without --json emit a
    human-readable transcript as a single text block.)
  - Progress for long runs (export, transcribe) goes to STDERR; stdout stays
    clean for the final result.
  - Error:   {"error": {"code", "message", "hint"?, "status"?}} on stderr,
             non-zero exit.

Contract commands (the same on every capability):
  telegram stub                                 One-line awareness text.
  telegram manifest --json                      Machine-readable declaration.
  telegram connections                          Where every connection's values
                                                 resolve from — tier, source,
                                                 secrets masked (local, no network).
  telegram guide [<topic>]                      Guide topics / one guide body,
                                                 fetched live from the docs base.
  telegram ids list|get <l>|set <l> <v>|rm <l>  The project identifiers envelope
                [--note <text>]                  (.capabilities/telegram/identifiers.json).
  telegram refs                                 Menu of the project's reference
                                                 files for this capability.

Exit codes:
  0  success
  2  auth — missing/invalid credentials, session expired, not logged in
  3  not found — the chat or entity could not be resolved
  4  policy refusal — disabled by project policy (.capabilities/settings.json),
     or `send` on a read-only connection — ask the user, never lift the gate
     yourself
  5  server / network — Telegram unreachable, flood-wait, Deepgram 5xx
  6  input / validation — a malformed argument, a bad date

Quirks worth knowing:
  - This is a full-account MTProto session — a personal user account, so it
    sees everything that account sees. The session file is auth material — it
    grants account access; keep it out of the repo.
  - A flood-wait (too many requests) surfaces as exit 5 with the wait seconds
    in the message; back off and retry later.
"""

import argparse
import asyncio
import json
import os
import sys
from datetime import datetime, timezone
from pathlib import Path
from typing import NoReturn

from telethon import TelegramClient
from telethon.errors import FloodWaitError, RPCError
from telethon.errors.rpcerrorlist import (
    ApiIdInvalidError,
    AuthKeyUnregisteredError,
    UsernameInvalidError,
    UsernameNotOccupiedError,
)
from telethon.tl.types import Channel, Chat, User

# --- Capability declaration (protocol 2) — one home for every contract fact --

NAME = "telegram"
PROTOCOL = 2
SUMMARY = ("Telegram CLI over a personal MTProto account — read/search a chat, "
           "send, export history to JSON, transcribe voice/audio. Stateful — "
           "run `telegram doctor` first.")
SCOPE = "user"   # credential scope: "project" | "user"
CRED_KEYS = [    # the implicit default connection; a registry entry supplies these per id
    {"key": "TELEGRAM_API_ID", "secret": False, "required": True,
     "note": "numeric app id from my.telegram.org/apps"},
    {"key": "TELEGRAM_API_HASH", "secret": True, "required": True,
     "note": "app hash from my.telegram.org/apps"},
    {"key": "TELEGRAM_SESSION", "secret": False, "required": False,
     "note": "session file path; default $XDG_STATE_HOME/telegram/session"},
    {"key": "DEEPGRAM_API_KEY", "secret": True, "required": False,
     "note": "voice/audio transcription"},
]
WRITE_VERBS = {"send"}   # the only domain verb that leaves the system — a message to a person
WRITE_DEFAULT = False    # a send leaves the system; granted per connection, explicitly
DOCS_BASE = ""      # upstream guides base URL; "" while no guides ship
TOPICS: list = []   # shipped guide topics
STATE = True       # True when the capability writes session/cache state
POST_INSTALL: list = []
_STATE_HOME = Path(os.environ.get("XDG_STATE_HOME") or (Path.home() / ".local" / "state"))

_CONFIG_HOME = Path(os.environ.get("XDG_CONFIG_HOME") or (Path.home() / ".config"))
CONFIG_DIR = _CONFIG_HOME / "telegram"
CREDENTIALS_ENV = CONFIG_DIR / "credentials.env"
DEFAULT_SESSION = _STATE_HOME / "telegram" / "session"
if (not DEFAULT_SESSION.with_suffix(".session").exists()
        and (CONFIG_DIR / "session.session").exists()):
    DEFAULT_SESSION = CONFIG_DIR / "session"  # an existing login keeps working from its current home


# --- I/O contract ------------------------------------------------------------

def _log(message: str) -> None:
    """Progress / diagnostics — stderr only, so stdout stays clean for data."""
    sys.stderr.write(message + "\n")
    sys.stderr.flush()


def _project_settings() -> dict:
    """Capability-owned, non-secret project config: .capabilities/<NAME>/settings.json."""
    envdir = _env_dir()
    if envdir is None:
        return {}
    try:
        return json.loads((envdir / "settings.json").read_text())
    except (OSError, ValueError):
        return {}


# >>> contract: capability core (generated — edit contract/preamble.py, run `capabilities sync-contract`) >>>

# --- Error reporting ---------------------------------------------------------

def _die(exit_code: int, code: str, message: str,
         hint: str | None = None, status: int | None = None) -> NoReturn:
    err: dict = {"code": code, "message": message}
    if hint:
        err["hint"] = hint
    if status is not None:
        err["status"] = status
    sys.stderr.write(json.dumps({"error": err}, ensure_ascii=False) + "\n")
    sys.exit(exit_code)


def _emit(value) -> None:
    if isinstance(value, str):
        sys.stdout.write(value)
        if value and not value.endswith("\n"):
            sys.stdout.write("\n")
    else:
        sys.stdout.write(json.dumps(value, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2) + "\n")


# --- Project / file plumbing -------------------------------------------------

def _parse_env_file(path: Path) -> dict:
    """Parse a KEY=VALUE env/dotenv file. Missing/unreadable file -> {}."""
    out: dict = {}
    try:
        text = path.read_text()
    except OSError:
        return out
    for line in text.splitlines():
        line = line.strip()
        if not line or line.startswith("#") or "=" not in line:
            continue
        k, v = line.split("=", 1)
        k = k.strip()
        if k.startswith("export "):
            k = k[len("export "):].strip()
        out[k] = v.strip().strip('"').strip("'")
    return out


def _project_root() -> Path | None:
    """Nearest project root, walking up from $CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR (else cwd):
    the first directory holding .capabilities/, .env(.local), or .git.
    $HOME is never a project root (the machine registry lives there)."""
    start = os.environ.get("CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR") or os.getcwd()
    here = Path(start).resolve()
    home = Path.home().resolve()
    for d in (here, *here.parents):
        if d == home:
            return None
        if ((d / ".capabilities").is_dir() or (d / ".env").exists()
                or (d / ".env.local").exists() or (d / ".git").is_dir()):
            return d
    return None


def _project_env() -> dict:
    """Project .env(.local) at the project root. .env.local overrides .env."""
    root = _project_root()
    if root is None:
        return {}
    merged = _parse_env_file(root / ".env")
    merged.update(_parse_env_file(root / ".env.local"))  # .local wins
    return merged


def _gate() -> None:
    """absent → run; enabled → run; disabled → exit 4. Unreadable never blocks."""
    root = _project_root()
    if root is None:
        return
    gate_file = root / ".capabilities" / "settings.json"
    try:
        entry = json.loads(gate_file.read_text()).get("capabilities", {}).get(NAME)
    except (OSError, ValueError):
        return
    if isinstance(entry, dict) and entry.get("enabled") is False:
        _die(4, "disabled",
             f"{NAME} is disabled in this project ({gate_file})",
             "Do not enable it yourself — ask the user whether to enable it, then stop.")


def _env_dir() -> Path | None:
    """The capability's envelope dir in the project: .capabilities/<NAME>/."""
    root = _project_root()
    return (root / ".capabilities" / NAME) if root is not None else None


def _state_dir() -> Path:
    """State follows the scope of the credentials that minted it; project state
    lands inside the envelope only where .capabilities/ already exists."""
    if SCOPE == "project":
        root = _project_root()
        if root is not None and (root / ".capabilities").is_dir():
            return root / ".capabilities" / NAME / "state"
    return _STATE_HOME / NAME


# --- Capability contract (protocol 2) — the declaration surface --------------

def _docs_base() -> str:
    key = f"{NAME.upper()}_DOCS_BASE"
    return (_project_env().get(key)
            or _parse_env_file(CREDENTIALS_ENV).get(key)
            or os.environ.get(key)
            or DOCS_BASE)


def _cmd_guide(argv: list[str]) -> None:
    if not argv:
        _emit(sorted(TOPICS)); return
    topic = argv[0]
    if topic not in TOPICS:
        _die(3, "not_found", f"no guide topic {topic!r}",
             f"topics: {', '.join(sorted(TOPICS)) or 'none shipped'}")
    import httpx as _hx
    url = _docs_base().rstrip("/") + "/" + topic + ".md"
    cache_dir = _STATE_HOME / NAME / "guides"
    cache, etag_f = cache_dir / f"{topic}.md", cache_dir / f"{topic}.etag"
    headers = {}
    if cache.exists() and etag_f.exists():
        headers["If-None-Match"] = etag_f.read_text().strip()
    try:
        resp = _hx.get(url, headers=headers, timeout=10.0, follow_redirects=True)
        if resp.status_code == 200:
            cache_dir.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)
            cache.write_text(resp.text)
            if resp.headers.get("etag"):
                etag_f.write_text(resp.headers["etag"])
            _emit(resp.text); return
        if resp.status_code == 304 and cache.exists():
            _emit(cache.read_text()); return
        if resp.status_code == 404:
            _die(3, "not_found", f"guide {topic!r} missing upstream", url)
        raise _hx.HTTPError(f"upstream returned {resp.status_code}")
    except _hx.HTTPError as e:
        if cache.exists():
            sys.stderr.write(json.dumps(
                {"warning": f"upstream unreachable; serving cached copy ({e})"},
                ensure_ascii=False) + "\n")
            _emit(cache.read_text()); return
        _die(5, "network_error", f"could not fetch guide {topic!r}; no cache exists", url)


def _cmd_ids(argv: list[str]) -> None:
    sub = argv[0] if argv else "list"
    envdir = _env_dir()
    ids_file = (envdir / "identifiers.json") if envdir else None
    data: dict = {}
    if ids_file and ids_file.exists():
        try:
            data = json.loads(ids_file.read_text())
        except ValueError:
            _die(6, "bad_envelope", f"{ids_file} is not valid JSON")
    if sub == "list":
        _emit(data); return
    if sub == "get":
        if len(argv) < 2 or argv[1] not in data:
            _die(3, "not_found", "unknown identifier label",
                 f"`{NAME} ids list` shows the labels")
        _emit((data[argv[1]] or {}).get("value")); return
    if sub == "set":
        if len(argv) < 3:
            _die(6, "input", f"usage: {NAME} ids set <label> <value> [--note <text>]")
        if envdir is None or not envdir.parent.is_dir():
            _die(6, "no_envelope", "no .capabilities/ envelope in this project",
                 "run `capabilities init` first")
        label, raw = argv[1], argv[2]
        try:
            value = json.loads(raw)
        except ValueError:
            value = raw
        note = ""
        if "--note" in argv:
            ni = argv.index("--note")
            if ni + 1 >= len(argv):
                _die(6, "input", "--note needs a value")
            note = argv[ni + 1]
        data[label] = {"value": value, "note": note or (data.get(label) or {}).get("note", "")}
        envdir.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)
        ids_file.write_text(json.dumps(data, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2, sort_keys=True) + "\n")
        _emit({"set": label}); return
    if sub == "rm":
        if len(argv) < 2 or argv[1] not in data:
            _die(3, "not_found", "unknown identifier label",
                 f"`{NAME} ids list` shows the labels")
        del data[argv[1]]
        ids_file.write_text(json.dumps(data, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2, sort_keys=True) + "\n")
        _emit({"removed": argv[1]}); return
    _die(6, "input", f"unknown ids subcommand {sub!r}", f"{NAME} ids list|get|set|rm")


def _cmd_refs() -> None:
    envdir = _env_dir()
    refdir = (envdir / "reference") if envdir else None
    out = []
    if refdir and refdir.is_dir():
        for md in sorted(refdir.glob("*.md")):
            name = desc = None
            try:
                lines = md.read_text().splitlines()
            except OSError:
                continue
            if lines and lines[0].strip() == "---":
                for line in lines[1:30]:
                    if line.strip() == "---":
                        break
                    if line.startswith("name:"):
                        name = line.split(":", 1)[1].strip()
                    elif line.startswith("description:"):
                        desc = line.split(":", 1)[1].strip()
            if name:
                out.append({"name": name, "description": desc or "", "path": str(md)})
    _emit(out)


def _contract(argv: list[str]) -> None:
    """Dispatch the contract verbs; domain verbs fall through to the CLI's own
    parser. Runs after _gate(), before any credential is resolved."""
    cmd = argv[0] if argv else ""
    if cmd == "stub":
        _emit(f"{SUMMARY} Run `{NAME} help`.")
    elif cmd == "manifest":
        _emit({"name": NAME, "protocol": PROTOCOL, "summary": SUMMARY,
               "credentials": {"scope": SCOPE, "keys": CRED_KEYS},
               "docs": {"base": DOCS_BASE, "topics": sorted(TOPICS)},
               "state": STATE, "post_install": POST_INSTALL})
    elif cmd == "guide":
        _cmd_guide(argv[1:])
    elif cmd == "ids":
        _cmd_ids(argv[1:])
    elif cmd == "refs":
        _cmd_refs()
    elif cmd == "connections":
        _cmd_connections()
    else:
        return
    sys.exit(0)

# <<< contract: capability core <<<


# >>> contract: connections (generated — edit contract/preamble.py, run `capabilities sync-contract`) >>>

def _resolve_env_key(key: str) -> tuple[str | None, str | None, Path | None]:
    """Resolve one env key through cascade tiers 2-4: project .env(.local) →
    user credentials.env → process env. Returns (value, tier, source)."""
    root = _project_root()
    if root is not None:
        for fname in (".env.local", ".env"):
            val = _parse_env_file(root / fname).get(key)
            if val:
                return val, "project", root / fname
    val = _parse_env_file(CREDENTIALS_ENV).get(key)
    if val:
        return val, "user", CREDENTIALS_ENV
    val = os.environ.get(key)
    if val:
        return val, "env", None
    return None, None, None


def _mask(value: str) -> str:
    return ("…" + value[-4:]) if len(value) >= 8 else "****"


def _connections_registry() -> tuple[dict | None, Path | None]:
    """The connections envelope and its path: project envelope first, else the
    user config home. First found wins, never merged; (None, None) when neither
    declares one (the implicit default connection applies)."""
    envdir = _env_dir()
    candidates = ([envdir / "connections.json"] if envdir else []) + \
                 [_CONFIG_HOME / NAME / "connections.json"]
    for reg_file in candidates:
        if not reg_file.is_file():
            continue
        try:
            raw = json.loads(reg_file.read_text())
        except (ValueError, OSError) as e:
            _die(6, "bad_config", f"cannot read {reg_file}: {e}")
        if not isinstance(raw, dict) or not isinstance(raw.get("connections"), dict) \
                or not raw["connections"]:
            _die(6, "bad_config", f"{reg_file} is not a connections envelope",
                 'expected {"default": "<id>", "connections": { ... }}')
        return raw, reg_file
    return None, None


def _select_connection(reg: dict | None, wanted: str | None) -> tuple[str, dict | None]:
    """flag → default pointer → sole entry → die 6. No registry → the implicit
    default. A connection's own `address` field selects it too (used where a
    connection carries a human-recognizable address; absent fields never match)."""
    if reg is None:
        if wanted and wanted != "default":
            _die(6, "unknown_connection",
                 "no connections registry; the sole connection is 'default'",
                 "the implicit default resolves from the credential cascade")
        return "default", None
    conns = reg["connections"]
    if wanted:
        if wanted in conns:
            return wanted, conns[wanted]
        for cid, entry in conns.items():
            if (entry or {}).get("address", "").lower() == wanted.lower():
                return cid, entry
        _die(6, "unknown_connection", f"no connection matches {wanted!r}",
             f"known: {', '.join(conns)}")
    default = reg.get("default")
    if default:
        if default not in conns:
            _die(6, "bad_default", f"default points to unknown connection {default!r}",
                 f"known: {', '.join(conns)}")
        return default, conns[default]
    if len(conns) == 1:
        cid = next(iter(conns))
        return cid, conns[cid]
    _die(6, "ambiguous_connection",
         f"registry defines {len(conns)} connections and no default; "
         f"pass --connection <id>",
         f"known: {', '.join(conns)}")


def _write_gate(conn_id: str, allow_write: bool, verb: str) -> None:
    """Policy from the committed registry; nothing in the cascade lifts it."""
    if verb in WRITE_VERBS and not allow_write:
        _die(4, "read_only",
             f"connection {conn_id!r} does not allow writes",
             "Do not lift the gate yourself — ask the user; granting is "
             "`allow_write: true` on this connection in connections.json.")


def _key_report(key: str, secret: bool, required: bool,
                value: str | None, tier: str | None, source) -> dict:
    return {"key": key, "secret": secret, "required": required,
            "set": bool(value), "tier": tier if value else None,
            "source": str(source) if (value and source) else None,
            "value": (_mask(value) if secret else value) if value else None}


def _missing_required(keys: list) -> list:
    """Required report rows (from _key_report) that did not resolve through the
    cascade — empty ⇒ credentials present. The primitive behind doctor's
    network-free readiness gate, read from the same per-key resolution
    `connections` reports, so the gate and the report can never disagree."""
    return [k["key"] for k in keys if k["required"] and not k["set"]]


def _doctor_gate(report: dict, wanted: str | None) -> None:
    """doctor's network-free readiness gate. Refuse with exit 2 — naming the
    unresolved required keys, before any round-trip — when a connection under
    test cannot resolve its required config through the cascade, so readiness is
    judged by the same resolution `connections` reports, never a parallel check.
    Checks the selected connection, else every connection in the report."""
    conns = report.get("connections") or {}
    targets = [wanted] if (wanted and wanted in conns) else list(conns)
    problems: dict = {}
    for cid in targets:
        miss = _missing_required((conns.get(cid) or {}).get("keys") or [])
        if miss:
            problems[cid] = miss
    if problems:
        detail = "; ".join(f"{c}: {', '.join(ks)}" for c, ks in sorted(problems.items()))
        _die(2, "credentials_missing",
             f"unresolved required config — {detail}",
             f"set each in the project .env/.env.local, the user credentials.env, "
             f"or process env; `{NAME} connections` shows where every value resolves")

# <<< contract: connections <<<


# --- Connections / credentials ----------------------------------------------

def _build_cfg(cid: str, entry: dict | None,
               session_flag: str | None) -> tuple[dict | None, dict | None]:
    """Materialize one connection's client config. Returns (cfg, problem) —
    problem is an error dict rather than a die, so doctor reports every
    connection instead of stopping at the first. The session is not a flat
    token: api id + app hash identify the app, a per-connection session FILE
    holds the login. The implicit default keeps its established session
    location; a named connection's session lives at <state-dir>/<id>/session.
    --session / TELEGRAM_SESSION is the one-shot override either way."""
    if entry is None:   # the implicit default — flat keys through the cascade
        api_id = _resolve_env_key("TELEGRAM_API_ID")[0]
        api_hash = _resolve_env_key("TELEGRAM_API_HASH")[0]
        missing = [k for k, v in (("TELEGRAM_API_ID", api_id),
                                   ("TELEGRAM_API_HASH", api_hash)) if not v]
        if missing:
            return None, {
                "exit": 2, "code": "missing_credentials",
                "message": f"unset: {', '.join(missing)}",
                "hint": f"create an app at my.telegram.org/apps, then set them in a "
                        f"project .env(.local), {CREDENTIALS_ENV}, or the environment "
                        f"— or declare a connections registry "
                        f"(.capabilities/{NAME}/connections.json)"}
        session = (session_flag or _resolve_env_key("TELEGRAM_SESSION")[0]
                   or str(DEFAULT_SESSION))
        allow_write = WRITE_DEFAULT
    else:
        api_id = entry.get("api_id")
        if api_id is None:
            return None, {"exit": 6, "code": "incomplete_connection",
                          "message": f"connection {cid!r} is missing 'api_id'"}
        secret_env = entry.get("secret_env")
        if not secret_env:
            return None, {"exit": 6, "code": "no_secret_env",
                          "message": f"connection {cid!r} is missing 'secret_env'"}
        api_hash = _resolve_env_key(secret_env)[0]
        if not api_hash:
            return None, {
                "exit": 2, "code": "missing_secret",
                "message": f"env var {secret_env} (for connection {cid!r}) is unset",
                "hint": f"set {secret_env} in a project .env / .env.local, "
                        f"{CREDENTIALS_ENV}, or the environment"}
        session = (session_flag or entry.get("session")
                   or str(_state_dir() / cid / "session"))
        allow_write = bool(entry.get("allow_write", WRITE_DEFAULT))
    try:
        api_id_int = int(str(api_id))
    except (TypeError, ValueError):
        return None, {"exit": 6, "code": "bad_api_id",
                      "message": f"api id for connection {cid!r} must be an integer",
                      "hint": "copy the numeric App api_id from my.telegram.org/apps"}
    return {"id": cid, "api_id": api_id_int, "api_hash": api_hash,
            "session": session, "allow_write": allow_write}, None


def _load_config(wanted: str | None, session_flag: str | None) -> dict:
    reg, _ = _connections_registry()
    cid, entry = _select_connection(reg, wanted)
    cfg, problem = _build_cfg(cid, entry, session_flag)
    if problem:
        _die(problem["exit"], problem["code"], problem["message"], problem.get("hint"))
    return cfg


def _connections_report() -> dict:
    """The resolution report — every connection, every value, its winning tier
    and source, secrets masked. Local only: no network, no login attempt."""
    reg, reg_path = _connections_registry()
    report: dict = {"default": None, "connections": {}}
    if reg is None:
        keys = []
        for k in CRED_KEYS:
            value, tier, source = _resolve_env_key(k["key"])
            keys.append(_key_report(k["key"], k["secret"], k["required"],
                                    value, tier, source))
        report["default"] = "default"
        report["connections"]["default"] = {"allow_write": WRITE_DEFAULT, "keys": keys}
        return report
    conns = reg["connections"]
    report["default"] = reg.get("default") or \
        (next(iter(conns)) if len(conns) == 1 else None)
    for cid, entry in conns.items():
        entry = entry if isinstance(entry, dict) else {}
        keys = []
        api_id = entry.get("api_id")
        keys.append(_key_report("api_id", False, True,
                                str(api_id) if api_id is not None else None,
                                "connection", reg_path))
        secret_env = entry.get("secret_env")
        if secret_env:
            value, tier, source = _resolve_env_key(secret_env)
            keys.append(_key_report(secret_env, True, True, value, tier, source))
        else:
            keys.append(_key_report("secret_env", False, True, None, None, None))
        session = entry.get("session") or str(_state_dir() / cid / "session")
        keys.append(_key_report("session", False, False, session, "connection", reg_path))
        report["connections"][cid] = {
            "allow_write": bool(entry.get("allow_write", WRITE_DEFAULT)),
            "keys": keys}
    return report


def _cmd_connections() -> None:
    _emit(_connections_report())


def make_client(cfg: dict) -> TelegramClient:
    """Build a client from a resolved connection config — the api id + app hash
    identify the app, the session FILE holds the persisted login."""
    session_path = Path(cfg["session"]).expanduser()
    session_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)
    return TelegramClient(str(session_path), cfg["api_id"], cfg["api_hash"])


def load_deepgram_key() -> str:
    key = _resolve_env_key("DEEPGRAM_API_KEY")[0]
    if not key:
        _die(2, "missing_deepgram_key",
             f"DEEPGRAM_API_KEY not found in a project .env, {CREDENTIALS_ENV}, or the environment",
             "add DEEPGRAM_API_KEY=<key> to the user config or a project .env to use `telegram transcribe`")
    return key


# --- Entities ----------------------------------------------------------------

def entity_label(ent) -> str:
    if isinstance(ent, User):
        name = " ".join(filter(None, [ent.first_name, ent.last_name])) or "(no name)"
        uname = f" @{ent.username}" if ent.username else ""
        return f"{name}{uname}"
    if isinstance(ent, (Chat, Channel)):
        return getattr(ent, "title", None) or "(untitled)"
    return str(ent)


async def resolve_chat(client: TelegramClient, chat: str):
    try:
        if chat.lstrip("-").isdigit():
            return await client.get_entity(int(chat))
        if chat.startswith("@") or chat.startswith("+"):
            return await client.get_entity(chat)
        lowered = chat.lower()
        async for dialog in client.iter_dialogs():
            if dialog.name and lowered in dialog.name.lower():
                return dialog.entity
        return await client.get_entity(chat)
    except (ValueError, UsernameNotOccupiedError, UsernameInvalidError):
        _die(3, "chat_not_found",
             f"could not resolve chat: {chat!r}",
             "pass an @username, +phone, numeric id, or a title from `telegram chats`")


async def _require_auth(client: TelegramClient) -> None:
    await client.connect()
    if not await client.is_user_authorized():
        await client.disconnect()
        _die(2, "not_authorized", "not logged in to Telegram", "run: telegram login")


def _parse_since(since: str | None) -> datetime | None:
    if not since:
        return None
    try:
        return datetime.fromisoformat(since).astimezone(timezone.utc)
    except ValueError:
        _die(6, "bad_date", f"--since is not an ISO datetime: {since!r}",
             "use e.g. 2026-06-01 or 2026-06-01T09:00")


# --- Commands ----------------------------------------------------------------

async def _check_connection(cfg: dict) -> dict:
    """One connection's authenticated round-trip, reported rather than died —
    doctor covers every connection, so a broken one becomes a finding, not a
    stop. Proves creds resolved, Telegram reachable, session authorized."""
    client = make_client(cfg)
    try:
        await client.connect()
        if not await client.is_user_authorized():
            return {"ok": False, "category": 2, "error": "not logged in",
                    "hint": f"run: telegram login --connection {cfg['id']}"}
        me = await client.get_me()
        return {"ok": True, "reachable": True,
                "account": entity_label(me), "id": me.id}
    except (ApiIdInvalidError, AuthKeyUnregisteredError) as e:
        return {"ok": False, "category": 2,
                "error": f"Telegram rejected the session/credentials: {e.__class__.__name__}",
                "hint": "run `telegram login` to re-authenticate"}
    except FloodWaitError as e:
        return {"ok": False, "category": 5,
                "error": f"flood wait — wait {e.seconds}s before retrying"}
    except (RPCError, ConnectionError, OSError) as e:
        return {"ok": False, "category": 5, "error": f"cannot reach Telegram: {e}"}
    finally:
        await client.disconnect()


def cmd_doctor(wanted: str | None) -> None:
    """Every connection's cheapest authenticated round-trip — the bare cascade,
    or just the one named by --connection. Exit 0 only when every examined
    connection is healthy, else the first failure's category."""
    _doctor_gate(_connections_report(), wanted)
    reg, _ = _connections_registry()
    if wanted is not None or reg is None:
        targets = [_select_connection(reg, wanted)]
    else:
        targets = list(reg["connections"].items())
    connections: dict = {}
    fail_exit = 0
    for cid, entry in targets:
        cfg, problem = _build_cfg(cid, entry, None)
        if problem:
            res = {"ok": False, "category": problem["exit"], "error": problem["message"]}
            if problem.get("hint"):
                res["hint"] = problem["hint"]
        else:
            res = asyncio.run(_check_connection(cfg))
        if not res.get("ok") and not fail_exit:
            fail_exit = res.get("category") or 5
        res.pop("category", None)
        connections[cid] = res
    _emit({"ok": fail_exit == 0, "connections": connections})
    if fail_exit:
        sys.exit(fail_exit)


async def cmd_login(cfg: dict) -> dict:
    client = make_client(cfg)
    await client.start()  # interactive: phone + code (+ 2FA password if set)
    me = await client.get_me()
    await client.disconnect()
    return {"ok": True, "connection": cfg["id"],
            "logged_in_as": entity_label(me), "id": me.id}


async def cmd_whoami(cfg: dict) -> dict:
    client = make_client(cfg)
    await _require_auth(client)
    me = await client.get_me()
    await client.disconnect()
    return {"account": entity_label(me), "id": me.id,
            "phone": f"+{me.phone}" if me.phone else None,
            "username": me.username}


async def cmd_chats(cfg: dict, limit: int) -> list[dict]:
    client = make_client(cfg)
    await _require_auth(client)
    out: list[dict] = []
    async for dialog in client.iter_dialogs(limit=limit):
        ent = dialog.entity
        out.append({
            "id": dialog.id,
            "kind": type(ent).__name__,
            "name": dialog.name or "(untitled)",
            "unread": dialog.unread_count or 0,
        })
    await client.disconnect()
    return out


def msg_to_dict(m) -> dict:
    return {
        "id": m.id,
        "date": m.date.astimezone(timezone.utc).isoformat() if m.date else None,
        "sender_id": m.sender_id,
        "sender": entity_label(m.sender) if m.sender else None,
        "text": m.message or "",
        "reply_to": m.reply_to_msg_id,
    }


def _render_transcript(header: str, messages: list) -> str:
    lines = [header]
    for m in messages:
        ts = m.date.astimezone(timezone.utc).strftime("%Y-%m-%d %H:%M") if m.date else "?"
        who = entity_label(m.sender) if m.sender else f"id={m.sender_id}"
        text = (m.message or "").replace("\n", " ⏎ ")
        lines.append(f"[{ts}] {who}: {text}")
    return "\n".join(lines)


async def cmd_read(cfg, chat: str, limit: int, since: str | None, as_json: bool):
    client = make_client(cfg)
    await _require_auth(client)
    entity = await resolve_chat(client, chat)
    since_dt = _parse_since(since)
    messages = []
    async for m in client.iter_messages(entity, limit=limit):
        if since_dt and m.date and m.date < since_dt:
            break
        messages.append(m)
    messages.reverse()
    await client.disconnect()
    if as_json:
        return [msg_to_dict(m) for m in messages]
    return _render_transcript(
        f"# {entity_label(entity)}  ({len(messages)} messages)", messages)


async def cmd_search(cfg, chat: str, query: str, limit: int, as_json: bool):
    client = make_client(cfg)
    await _require_auth(client)
    entity = await resolve_chat(client, chat)
    messages = []
    async for m in client.iter_messages(entity, search=query, limit=limit):
        messages.append(m)
    messages.reverse()
    await client.disconnect()
    if as_json:
        return [msg_to_dict(m) for m in messages]
    return _render_transcript(
        f"# {entity_label(entity)}  search: {query!r}  ({len(messages)} hits)", messages)


async def cmd_send(cfg, chat: str, text: str) -> dict:
    client = make_client(cfg)
    await _require_auth(client)
    entity = await resolve_chat(client, chat)
    sent = await client.send_message(entity, text)
    await client.disconnect()
    return {"sent_id": sent.id, "to": entity_label(entity)}


# --- Export ------------------------------------------------------------------

def _classify_media(m):
    """Return (kind, details_dict_or_None). Kind is one of:
    text, voice, audio, photo, video, video_note, sticker, document, webpage, poll, contact, geo, other, service.
    """
    if m.action is not None:
        return "service", {"action": type(m.action).__name__}
    if m.voice:
        doc = m.document
        return "voice", {
            "mime_type": getattr(doc, "mime_type", None),
            "size_bytes": getattr(doc, "size", None),
            "duration_sec": next(
                (a.duration for a in (doc.attributes if doc else []) if hasattr(a, "duration")),
                None,
            ),
        }
    if m.audio:
        doc = m.document
        title = None
        performer = None
        for a in doc.attributes if doc else []:
            title = getattr(a, "title", None) or title
            performer = getattr(a, "performer", None) or performer
        return "audio", {
            "mime_type": getattr(doc, "mime_type", None),
            "size_bytes": getattr(doc, "size", None),
            "title": title,
            "performer": performer,
        }
    if m.video_note:
        return "video_note", {"size_bytes": getattr(m.document, "size", None)}
    if m.video:
        return "video", {
            "mime_type": getattr(m.document, "mime_type", None),
            "size_bytes": getattr(m.document, "size", None),
        }
    if m.sticker:
        return "sticker", {"mime_type": getattr(m.document, "mime_type", None)}
    if m.photo:
        return "photo", {"photo_id": getattr(m.photo, "id", None)}
    if m.document:
        doc = m.document
        filename = None
        for a in doc.attributes:
            filename = getattr(a, "file_name", None) or filename
        return "document", {
            "mime_type": getattr(doc, "mime_type", None),
            "size_bytes": getattr(doc, "size", None),
            "filename": filename,
        }
    if m.web_preview:
        return "webpage", {"url": getattr(m.web_preview, "url", None)}
    if m.poll:
        return "poll", {"question": getattr(m.poll.poll, "question", None)}
    if m.contact:
        return "contact", {}
    if m.geo:
        return "geo", {}
    if m.media is not None:
        return "other", {"type": type(m.media).__name__}
    return "text", None


def _find_existing_media(media_dir: Path, msg_id: int) -> Path | None:
    for p in media_dir.glob(f"{msg_id}.*"):
        if p.is_file():
            return p
    return None


async def cmd_export(cfg, chat: str, out_path: str, media_dir: str | None,
                     limit: int | None, since: str | None,
                     download_photos: bool, download_stickers: bool,
                     download_videos: bool, download_documents: bool) -> dict:
    client = make_client(cfg)
    await _require_auth(client)

    entity = await resolve_chat(client, chat)
    out = Path(out_path).expanduser().resolve()
    out.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)

    if media_dir is None:
        media_dir_path = out.parent / "media"
    else:
        media_dir_path = Path(media_dir).expanduser().resolve()
    media_dir_path.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)

    download_types = {"voice", "audio"}
    if download_photos:
        download_types.add("photo")
    if download_stickers:
        download_types.add("sticker")
    if download_videos:
        download_types.update({"video", "video_note"})
    if download_documents:
        download_types.add("document")

    prior_transcriptions: dict[int, dict] = {}
    if out.exists():
        try:
            prev = json.loads(out.read_text())
            for pm in prev.get("messages", []):
                tr = pm.get("transcription")
                if tr and isinstance(tr, dict) and "text" in tr and pm.get("id") is not None:
                    prior_transcriptions[pm["id"]] = tr
        except Exception:
            pass

    since_dt = _parse_since(since)
    me = await client.get_me()

    chat_meta = {
        "id": getattr(entity, "id", None),
        "title": entity_label(entity),
        "type": type(entity).__name__,
        "username": getattr(entity, "username", None),
    }

    messages_out: list[dict] = []
    iter_kwargs: dict = {}
    if limit:
        iter_kwargs["limit"] = limit

    count = 0
    dl_counts: dict[str, int] = {}
    progress_every = 100
    _log(f"Exporting from: {chat_meta['title']}  ({chat_meta['type']}, id={chat_meta['id']})")
    _log(f"Output:       {out}")
    _log(f"Media dir:    {media_dir_path}")
    _log(f"Downloading:  {sorted(download_types)}")
    if prior_transcriptions:
        _log(f"Preserving:   {len(prior_transcriptions)} existing transcription(s)")

    async for m in client.iter_messages(entity, **iter_kwargs):
        if since_dt and m.date and m.date < since_dt:
            break

        kind, media_meta = _classify_media(m)

        sender = None
        if m.sender is not None:
            sender = {
                "id": m.sender_id,
                "name": entity_label(m.sender),
                "username": getattr(m.sender, "username", None),
                "type": type(m.sender).__name__,
            }
        elif m.sender_id is not None:
            sender = {"id": m.sender_id, "name": None, "username": None, "type": None}

        fwd = None
        if m.forward is not None:
            fwd_name = None
            try:
                if m.forward.sender is not None:
                    fwd_name = entity_label(m.forward.sender)
                elif m.forward.chat is not None:
                    fwd_name = entity_label(m.forward.chat)
            except Exception:
                pass
            fwd = {
                "date": m.forward.date.astimezone(timezone.utc).isoformat() if m.forward.date else None,
                "from_id": getattr(m.forward, "sender_id", None) or getattr(m.forward, "chat_id", None),
                "from_name": fwd_name,
            }

        entry: dict = {
            "id": m.id,
            "date": m.date.astimezone(timezone.utc).isoformat() if m.date else None,
            "edited_at": m.edit_date.astimezone(timezone.utc).isoformat() if m.edit_date else None,
            "sender": sender,
            "reply_to_msg_id": m.reply_to_msg_id,
            "forward": fwd,
            "type": kind,
            "text": m.message or None,
            "media": media_meta,
        }

        if kind in download_types:
            existing = _find_existing_media(media_dir_path, m.id)
            try:
                if existing:
                    entry["media"] = entry["media"] or {}
                    entry["media"]["file_path"] = str(existing.resolve())
                else:
                    downloaded = await m.download_media(file=str(media_dir_path / str(m.id)))
                    if downloaded:
                        entry["media"] = entry["media"] or {}
                        entry["media"]["file_path"] = str(Path(downloaded).resolve())
                        dl_counts[kind] = dl_counts.get(kind, 0) + 1
                if kind in ("voice", "audio") and entry["media"] and entry["media"].get("file_path"):
                    entry["transcription"] = prior_transcriptions.get(m.id)
            except Exception as e:
                entry["media"] = entry["media"] or {}
                entry["media"]["download_error"] = repr(e)
                if kind in ("voice", "audio"):
                    entry["transcription"] = prior_transcriptions.get(m.id)

        messages_out.append(entry)
        count += 1
        if count % progress_every == 0:
            _log(f"  ... {count} messages  downloads so far: {dl_counts}")

    messages_out.reverse()

    payload = {
        "chat": chat_meta,
        "exported_at": datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat(),
        "exported_by": {"id": me.id, "name": entity_label(me), "username": me.username},
        "message_count": len(messages_out),
        "media_dir": str(media_dir_path),
        "media_policy": {
            "voice": True,
            "audio": True,
            "photos": download_photos,
            "stickers": download_stickers,
            "videos": download_videos,
            "documents": download_documents,
        },
        "schema_version": 2,
        "notes": (
            "Messages are stored newest-last. Voice/audio entries have a "
            "'transcription' field filled by `telegram transcribe`. Photos, stickers, "
            "videos, and documents (when downloaded per media_policy) have "
            "'media.file_path' pointing to local binary. Multimodal tools can "
            "read images directly; videos/documents are stored as-is for "
            "on-demand processing."
        ),
        "messages": messages_out,
    }
    out.write_text(json.dumps(payload, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2))
    await client.disconnect()
    _log(f"Done. {len(messages_out)} messages written. New downloads: {dl_counts}")
    return {
        "out": str(out),
        "media_dir": str(media_dir_path),
        "message_count": len(messages_out),
        "new_downloads": dl_counts,
    }


# --- Transcribe (Deepgram) ---------------------------------------------------

def _content_type_for(path: Path) -> str:
    ext = path.suffix.lower()
    return {
        ".ogg": "audio/ogg",
        ".oga": "audio/ogg",
        ".opus": "audio/ogg",
        ".mp3": "audio/mpeg",
        ".m4a": "audio/mp4",
        ".wav": "audio/wav",
        ".webm": "audio/webm",
        ".flac": "audio/flac",
    }.get(ext, "application/octet-stream")


def _deepgram_transcribe(audio_path: Path, api_key: str, model: str = "nova-3") -> dict:
    """Send one audio file to Deepgram; return a structured transcription dict.
    Maps an HTTP failure onto the exit-code taxonomy (2 auth, 5 server/network)."""
    import urllib.error
    import urllib.request

    params = (
        f"model={model}&detect_language=true&smart_format=true"
        f"&punctuate=true&paragraphs=true"
    )
    url = f"https://api.deepgram.com/v1/listen?{params}"
    data = audio_path.read_bytes()
    req = urllib.request.Request(
        url,
        data=data,
        method="POST",
        headers={
            "Authorization": f"Token {api_key}",
            "Content-Type": _content_type_for(audio_path),
        },
    )
    try:
        with urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=300) as resp:
            body = resp.read().decode("utf-8")
    except urllib.error.HTTPError as e:
        detail = e.read().decode("utf-8", errors="replace")
        raise RuntimeError(f"Deepgram HTTP {e.code}: {detail}") from e

    dg = json.loads(body)
    channels = dg.get("results", {}).get("channels", [])
    if not channels:
        raise RuntimeError(f"Deepgram returned no channels: {body[:500]}")
    alt = channels[0].get("alternatives", [{}])[0]
    text = (alt.get("paragraphs", {}) or {}).get("transcript") or alt.get("transcript") or ""
    detected_language = channels[0].get("detected_language")
    confidence = alt.get("confidence")

    return {
        "text": text.strip(),
        "language": detected_language,
        "confidence": confidence,
        "model": model,
        "provider": "deepgram",
        "transcribed_at": datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat(),
    }


def cmd_transcribe(json_path: str, force: bool, model: str) -> dict:
    api_key = load_deepgram_key()
    p = Path(json_path).expanduser().resolve()
    if not p.exists():
        _die(6, "file_not_found", f"export JSON does not exist: {p}",
             "pass the path to a JSON produced by `telegram export`")
    payload = json.loads(p.read_text())
    messages = payload.get("messages", [])

    to_do = []
    for idx, m in enumerate(messages):
        if m.get("type") not in ("voice", "audio"):
            continue
        file_path = (m.get("media") or {}).get("file_path")
        if not file_path:
            continue
        if not force and m.get("transcription") is not None:
            continue
        to_do.append((idx, m, Path(file_path)))

    if not to_do:
        _log("Nothing to transcribe (use --force to re-run).")
        return {"file": str(p), "transcribed": 0, "failed": 0, "pending": 0}

    _log(f"Transcribing {len(to_do)} file(s) with Deepgram (model={model})...")
    failures = 0
    for n, (idx, m, ap) in enumerate(to_do, 1):
        if not ap.exists():
            _log(f"  [{n}/{len(to_do)}] SKIP missing file: {ap}")
            m["transcription"] = {"error": f"file not found: {ap}"}
            failures += 1
            continue
        _log(f"  [{n}/{len(to_do)}] id={m['id']}  {ap.name}  ({ap.stat().st_size // 1024} KB)")
        try:
            result = _deepgram_transcribe(ap, api_key, model=model)
            m["transcription"] = result
            preview = (result["text"][:80] + "…") if len(result["text"]) > 80 else result["text"]
            _log(f"       → [{result.get('language')}] {preview}")
        except Exception as e:
            m["transcription"] = {"error": str(e)}
            failures += 1
            _log(f"       → ERROR: {e}")
        # incremental save so a crash doesn't lose prior work
        p.write_text(json.dumps(payload, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2))

    _log(f"Done. {len(to_do) - failures}/{len(to_do)} transcribed. File: {p}")
    return {
        "file": str(p),
        "transcribed": len(to_do) - failures,
        "failed": failures,
    }


# --- CLI ---------------------------------------------------------------------

def main() -> None:
    _gate()                      # every verb passes the project gate first
    _contract(sys.argv[1:])      # contract verbs; domain verbs fall through
    p = argparse.ArgumentParser(
        prog="telegram",
        description=__doc__,
        formatter_class=argparse.RawDescriptionHelpFormatter,
    )
    sub = p.add_subparsers(dest="cmd", required=True)

    sub.add_parser("help", help="print the full usage contract")
    sub.add_parser("doctor", help="health check: creds + reachability + session")
    sub.add_parser("login", help="interactive first-time auth (phone + code)")
    sub.add_parser("whoami", help="identity of the signed-in account")

    pc = sub.add_parser("chats", help="list recent dialogs")
    pc.add_argument("--limit", type=int, default=50)

    pr = sub.add_parser("read", help="read messages from a chat")
    pr.add_argument("chat")
    pr.add_argument("--limit", type=int, default=50)
    pr.add_argument("--since", help="ISO datetime; stop at this date")
    pr.add_argument("--json", action="store_true")

    ps = sub.add_parser("search", help="search inside a chat")
    ps.add_argument("chat")
    ps.add_argument("query")
    ps.add_argument("--limit", type=int, default=50)
    ps.add_argument("--json", action="store_true")

    pn = sub.add_parser("send", help="send a message")
    pn.add_argument("chat")
    pn.add_argument("text")

    pe = sub.add_parser("export", help="dump full chat history to JSON and download media")
    pe.add_argument("chat")
    pe.add_argument("--out", required=True, help="output JSON path")
    pe.add_argument("--media-dir", help="directory for downloaded media (default: alongside --out)")
    pe.add_argument("--limit", type=int, help="max messages (default: all)")
    pe.add_argument("--since", help="ISO datetime; stop at this date")
    pe.add_argument("--photos", action=argparse.BooleanOptionalAction, default=True,
                    help="download photos (default: on; --no-photos to skip)")
    pe.add_argument("--stickers", action=argparse.BooleanOptionalAction, default=True,
                    help="download stickers (default: on; --no-stickers to skip)")
    pe.add_argument("--videos", action="store_true",
                    help="also download videos + video-notes (default: off)")
    pe.add_argument("--documents", action="store_true",
                    help="also download documents (default: off)")

    pt = sub.add_parser("transcribe", help="fill transcription placeholders via Deepgram")
    pt.add_argument("json_path")
    pt.add_argument("--force", action="store_true", help="re-transcribe even if already filled")
    pt.add_argument("--model", default="nova-3", help="Deepgram model (default: nova-3)")

    # `--connection <id>` selects a connection; `--session <PATH>` overrides the
    # session-file path. Both are global, accepted anywhere on the line (extracted
    # before argparse so they work after the subcommand). `--session` is the flag
    # tier of the cascade and names a path, not a secret.
    argv = sys.argv[1:]
    session_flag: str | None = None
    connection_flag: str | None = None
    cleaned: list[str] = []
    i = 0
    while i < len(argv):
        a = argv[i]
        if a == "--session" and i + 1 < len(argv):
            session_flag = argv[i + 1]; i += 2; continue
        if a.startswith("--session="):
            session_flag = a.split("=", 1)[1]; i += 1; continue
        if a == "--connection" and i + 1 < len(argv):
            connection_flag = argv[i + 1]; i += 2; continue
        if a.startswith("--connection="):
            connection_flag = a.split("=", 1)[1]; i += 1; continue
        cleaned.append(a); i += 1

    args = p.parse_args(cleaned)

    if args.cmd == "help":
        sys.stdout.write((__doc__ or "").lstrip("\n"))
        return
    if args.cmd == "doctor":
        cmd_doctor(connection_flag)   # per-connection; emits and sets the exit code itself
        return
    if args.cmd == "transcribe":      # connection-independent: a local file + Deepgram
        _emit(cmd_transcribe(args.json_path, args.force, args.model))
        return

    cfg = _load_config(connection_flag, session_flag)
    _write_gate(cfg["id"], cfg["allow_write"], args.cmd)
    try:
        if args.cmd == "login":
            _emit(asyncio.run(cmd_login(cfg)))
        elif args.cmd == "whoami":
            _emit(asyncio.run(cmd_whoami(cfg)))
        elif args.cmd == "chats":
            _emit(asyncio.run(cmd_chats(cfg, args.limit)))
        elif args.cmd == "read":
            _emit(asyncio.run(cmd_read(cfg, args.chat, args.limit, args.since, args.json)))
        elif args.cmd == "search":
            _emit(asyncio.run(cmd_search(cfg, args.chat, args.query, args.limit, args.json)))
        elif args.cmd == "send":
            _emit(asyncio.run(cmd_send(cfg, args.chat, args.text)))
        elif args.cmd == "export":
            _emit(asyncio.run(cmd_export(
                cfg, args.chat, args.out, args.media_dir, args.limit, args.since,
                args.photos, args.stickers, args.videos, args.documents,
            )))
    except (ApiIdInvalidError, AuthKeyUnregisteredError) as e:
        _die(2, "auth_failed", f"Telegram rejected the session/credentials: {e.__class__.__name__}",
             "run `telegram login` to re-authenticate; verify TELEGRAM_API_ID / TELEGRAM_API_HASH")
    except FloodWaitError as e:
        _die(5, "flood_wait", f"Telegram rate limit — wait {e.seconds}s before retrying",
             "back off and retry later", status=420)
    except RPCError as e:
        _die(5, "rpc_error", f"Telegram RPC error: {e.__class__.__name__}: {e}",
             status=getattr(e, "code", None))
    except (ConnectionError, OSError) as e:
        _die(5, "network_error", f"network error reaching Telegram: {e}", "check connectivity")


if __name__ == "__main__":
    main()
